The paper proposes a method for quantization in ANN search, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) applications. The method involves a deep learning architecture with recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (ML) and natural language processing (NLP) fields. The paper also compares the proposed method with state-of-the-art approaches in image retrieval, which is a subfield of multimedia (MM) and computer vision (CV). Finally, the paper mentions that the proposed method can be trained in an end-to-end manner, which is a common feature of deep learning models in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL).
